Study Design: Observational Prospective Cross-sectional Study

Research Design: Qualitative and Quantitative

Primary Data type: Digital Survey

Secondary data Collections: Journals, Books, Various online available literatures

Study Location: West Bengal is on the eastern bottleneck of India, stretching from the Himalayas in the north to the Bay of Bengal in the south.
It lies between 85 degree 50 minutes and 89 degree 50 minutes east longitude, and 21 degrees 25 minutes and 27 degrees 13 minutes north latitude.

Population: 10.19 Crore.

Study and Questionnaire Language: English

 

Data Management and analysis: Data will be taken in the google form and will be stored in the excel file.
The whole survey will be done in the digital format.
The statistician will calculate the correlative measurements on the incidence rate, severity and mortality of breakthrough COVID19 infections.

The aim and research questions are highlighted below.

 

 Aim of This Research and Research Questions:

 1.

How many People are getting COVID 19 Positive result after first dose?

2.

How many people are getting COVID 19 Positive result after Second dose?

3.

How many People are getting COVID 19 Positive result after Precautions Dose?

4.

Duration between Jab and Disease Symptom appearance?

5.

Gender Based Analysis.

6.

Second wave and Third Waves in West Bengal will be included?

7.

Vaccine Immunity Vs Natural Immunity?

8.

Comparative measures between COVAXIN and CovidShield ?

9.
Delta Variant and Omicron Variant will be included ?

Comorbidity Analysis

11.

Population will be only within West Bengal

 12.

Duration: 2 months

Plan of the study:

We will conduct a digital survey based on the given questionnaire.
Followed by we will analyze the data of breakthrough COVID 19 infections incidence, severity and mortality.
The survey will be done among the population of West Bengal.
We will make a comparative analysis between the vaccines and we will find the answer of the above research questions.
